# Pulled Pork

Source (Main Recipe): https://heygrillhey.com/simple-smoked-pulled-pork/
Source (Rub): https://heygrillhey.com/best-sweet-rub-grilled-pork-chicken/

## In the Smoker
### Rub Ingredients
* 1/4 Cup Dark Brown Sugar
* 1 tbsp Salt
* 2 tsp Black Pepper
* 2 tsp Smoked Paprika
* 2 tsp Garlic Powder
* 2 tsp Onion Powder
* 1 tsp Ground Mustard
* 1 tsp Cayenne Pepper

### Timing
225F - 2hrs/lb
300F - 45-50min/lb (actually ended up being 1 hr/lb)
* 9lbs took 9 hours to get up to temp

### Instructions
* Make rub
* Coat pork with 3 tbsp of mustard
* Season on all sides with rub
* Put on grate, fat side up
* Smoke until second thermometer reads 200F
* Remove from smoker, put in foil pan, cover pan with foil.  Put pan in cooler for at least 1 hour
* Shred and Serve
